revisions.description: The private MIB module definition for Protected Ports MIB.

rlProtectedPortsTable.name: rlProtectedPortsTable
rlProtectedPortsTable.description: A table containing entries of protected ports configuration information

rlProtectedPortsEntry.name: rlProtectedPortsEntry
rlProtectedPortsEntry.description: A table entry of protected ports configuration information

rlProtectedPortType.name: rlProtectedPortType
rlProtectedPortType.description: Set port protected mode: not-protected, protected protected ports filter layer 2 traffic from other protected ports

rlProtectedPortCommunity.name: rlProtectedPortCommunity
rlProtectedPortCommunity.description: Associate protected port with community number which becoming active only when rlProtectedPortsStatus changed to protected protected community ports filter layer 2 traffic from protected ports and from other protected community ports, but do not filter layer 2 traffic from same community ports. value of 0 disassociate port from its community.

rlProtectedPortsStatusTable.name: rlProtectedPortsStatusTable
rlProtectedPortsStatusTable.description: A table containing entries of protected ports status

rlProtectedPortsStatusEntry.name: rlProtectedPortsStatusEntry
rlProtectedPortsStatusEntry.description: A table entry containing protected ports DB status information

rlProtectedPortEgressPorts.name: rlProtectedPortEgressPorts
rlProtectedPortEgressPorts.description: list of ports which are not filtered by protected port mechanism when traffic is forwarded from the specified ifIndex

rlProtectedPortsGlobalEnable.name: rlProtectedPortsGlobalEnable
rlProtectedPortsGlobalEnable.description: true - set all system fast ethernet ports to protected state false - set all system fast ethernet ports to not protected state
